reviews.text: Why am I just trying this place out? It's been so close all this time. I decided to try them because I was in the same strip center taking care of other things. The pies look amazing as soon as you walk in the door. I thought I would just get one or two to try. I walked out with four mini pies. My mom devoured the key lime. I thoroughly enjoyed the banana cream. We have the coconut and the I-40 left and I am excited to see how they taste. They really hit the spot.

Maybe our expectations were too high? We bought a stack of pies in the end. Some were good & some not.
Whenever we go to a new place we tell the employee ‚ÄúThis is our first time here‚Äù usually they are a little nicer & give us a rundown of what they offer. Not this time. The employee seemed to not care. She just said ok & stayed quiet. So we were busy looking around trying to figure out what things were. The sun really comes in & beams down on all the glass making it a little difficult to read some of the signage. I asked a few questions like what was the I-40 & what the prices were. I also asked if they offered other items. We ended up buying a stack of 4 pies to try. After we paid, I saw there were some other items for sale that we would‚Äôve included, but the employee seemed to ring us up so quickly we didn‚Äôt get a chance to add them to the order. I was still looking at other pies while she had wrapped up the 4 & said the total. We were the only customers in there so I was surprised by rush to move us along.
The ones we bought included Nanny‚Äôs pecan which was good, but the I-40 was waaaay too sweet, couldn‚Äôt taste anything but sugar. The custard pie was over baked. There‚Äôs definitely better ones on the market. Then we had the lemon. üçã Nice flavor & not too sweet.

I will say, I was a bit apprehensive about spending $40 on a pie for my wife's birthday.

1. Not a huge fan of banana cream pie

2. It's a pie....

BUT, this was thee best pie I have EVER had. The whole crust is like a sugar cookie and the filling wasn't just some banana floof like pudding or something.

If you have never tried anything from Buttermilk Sky I'd HIGHLY recommend!

My goodness these people know how to make pies. We tried the peanut butter, banana cream, cookie and french apple. I am not kidding you that peanut butter pie is the best think you will ever eat ever. That banana cream pie is the best I have EVER tasted. I will definitely be back here! Also the owners were just as sweet as their pies! AMAZING!

A place just for pies? Say less. The key lime and peanut butter cream are to die for. They have a large display case full of flavors... I think I need to try them all! Love that they offer mini pies, pie stacks, and even pies for nationwide delivery.
